    "longDesc": "Acute pharyngitis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Acute pharyngitis is a sudden, painful inflammation of the throat caused by either a viral or bacterial infection. You'll typically experience a sore throat, difficulty swallowing, and possibly fever—it's the painful condition that makes you feel like something is scratching the back of your throat. The code 'unspecified' simply means the doctor documented pharyngitis but didn't specify which type of germ caused it.",
