    "rawCode": "J410",
    "shortDesc": "Simple chronic bronchitis",
    "longDesc": "Simple chronic bronchitis",
    "plainEnglish": "Simple chronic bronchitis is a long-lasting inflammation of the airways in your lungs (the bronchi) that causes a persistent cough, usually with mucus or phlegm. This happens when you're repeatedly exposed to irritants like cigarette smoke, pollution, or dust over time, and your airways become swollen and produce extra mucus as a defense mechanism. Unlike acute bronchitis that comes and goes, this condition lasts for months or years and is most common in smokers or people with long-term environmental exposure.",
